description:
&lt;p&gt;Health Care Records Clerk - Based at ROYAL HAMPSHIRE COUNTY HOSPITAL, WINCHESTER&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Healthcare Records Department is responsible for the management, storage and provision of records for all outpatient clinics and admitted patients at Andover&lt;br /&gt;War Memorial Hospital, Basingstoke and North Hampshire Hospital and Royal Hampshire County Hospital, Winchester.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Department is looking to recruit Medical Records Clerks to work as part of a team of clerks, team leaders and supervisors that retrieve notes from the records library, prepare them for outpatient clinics or in-patient admissions and ensure that they are tracked and monitored correctly throughout the Trust’s hospital sites. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The work requires the lifting, carrying and moving of paper-based records throughout each day, some of which are stored at floor level and others may be on higher shelves only accessible with stools or ladders. Collections of records, boxes and even individual files may be heavy (up to 10kg). Records are stored in numerical order in an extensive library and need to be located, processed and returned accurately and quickly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Victoria.Wilkinson@hhft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
